title: George Osborne: Councils to keep £26bn from business rates
text:
George Osborne has insisted that HS2, the controversial new high-speed rail link, will be built through his own constituency despite fierce opposition, reports Deputy Political Editor Chris Ship.
Chris Ship @chrisshipitv Follow Osborne saying #hs2 must be built through his constituency despite those who live in it who oppose the new line
